50
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:22,480
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第五季  第八集

51
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:38,360
他不在  你是不是觉得很别扭
It's strange for you, isn't it? Without him here.

52
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:40,710
没什么别扭的  夫人
It's not strange, ma'am.

53
00:05:43,230 --> 00:05:46,130
莉安去辛辛那提敲定辩论的事了
LeAnn's in Cincinnati, trying to close the deal for the debate.

54
00:05:46,130 --> 00:05:48,480
等总统回来  就巡回全州  出席多场
The president will make a series of appearances across the state

55
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,890
拉票活动
as soon as he gets back.

56
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:53,340
如果他能挺过这个周末  有消息吗
If he survives the weekend. Anything?

57
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:54,550
那里不让带手机
No phones allowed.

58
00:05:55,550 --> 00:05:57,570
我们这是分头行动  各个击破
Well, we're dividing and conquering.

59
00:05:57,570 --> 00:05:59,140
这份对华贸易协定
This Chinese trade agreement

60
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:01,790
会让俄亥俄州选民非常开心的
is going to make Ohio voters very happy.

61
00:06:01,790 --> 00:06:03,270
能帮我们胜选
It could help us win.

62
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:06,030
-我不知道协议谈妥了  -就快谈妥了
- I didn't know the deal had closed. - Well, we're on the verge.

63
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:09,070
等总统到坎顿出席活动的时候可以当众宣布
The president can make the announcement in Canton when he appears.

64
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:11,370
不用了  我自己宣布就行
Oh, no, I'll be announcing myself...

65
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,720
毕竟是我谈定的
since I did the deal.

66
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,850
道格  你非常真诚
Doug, you are very sincere...

67
00:06:17,810 --> 00:06:19,140
对弗兰西斯也很忠诚
and very loyal to Francis.

68
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,740
我也忠于你  夫人
And loyal to you, ma'am.

69
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:21,790
我希望您知道这一点
I hope you know that.

70
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:25,240
其实你叫我克莱尔也是可以的
I don't mind it if you call me Claire, you know.

71
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,200
我这就带戴维斯女士进来
I'll show Ms. Davis in.

72
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:36,120
你好啊  简
Hi, Jane.

73
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,320
在会见部长之前  你能和我一起
Would you mind going over these numbers with me

74
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:39,950
再过一遍这些数字吗
before we meet with the minister?

75
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:42,260
我知道中方嘴上能接受的数字
I have what China says they'll settle for,

76
00:06:42,270 --> 00:06:44,200
也知道他们心里愿接受的数字
and what I know they'll settle for.

77
00:06:44,210 --> 00:06:46,980
我想感谢你在这件事上给我们的帮助
And listen, I want to thank you so much for helping us with this.

78
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:49,890
我就想看到安德伍德执政
I'd like to see an Underwood administration.

79
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:51,660
道格  没别的事了
Doug, that's all for now.

80
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:54,640
好的  夫人
Yes, ma'am.

81
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,950
{\pos(269.4,103.05)}圣达菲县
身份不明人员搜索

82
00:07:21,260 --> 00:07:24,450
-你可以给我看的  -我不想让你看
- You can show me. - I don't want to.

83
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:26,110
你不用这么保护我
You don't have to protect me.

84
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:31,090
她们每个人背后都有一段故事
Each of them has a story.

85
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:34,570
就算她们后来迷失了
Even if they got lost somewhere.

86
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,490
消失比你想得要困难
It's harder to disappear than you would think.

87
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,660
但瑞秋
But Rachel...

88
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:45,540
完全不见踪影
is nowhere.

89
00:07:55,730 --> 00:07:58,320
这脖子我一眼就认出来了
I recognize that neck.

90
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:03,070
弗兰克·安德伍德  真没想到
Frank Underwood, as I live and breathe.

91
00:08:03,930 --> 00:08:07,150
打赌你赢了
Well, I owe you this.

92
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,850
他不认为你会来
He didn't expect you to show up.

93
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:13,360
能见到老朋友总是很开心
I'm always happy to see old friends.

94
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:15,580
交新朋友也很开心  弗兰克·安德伍德
And make new ones. Frank Underwood.

95
00:08:15,580 --> 00:08:18,920
-本杰明·格兰特  -波利跳的那位  是啊
- Benjamin Grant. - Oh, of Pollyhop. Of course.

96
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:21,160
你是我对手的强烈支持者
You're a big supporter of my opponent.

97
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,480
他是个高瞻远瞩的人  也是我朋友
He's a forward-thinking guy and a friend,

98
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,810
他现在应该是总统
who should be president right now.

99
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:26,400
先生们  在这儿的时候
There's no talking politics or business

100
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:27,330
不能谈政治或生意
while we're here, gentlemen.

101
00:08:27,330 --> 00:08:30,150
是啊  我们可别用争吵荼毒了自然
Yes, we don't want to poison all this nature with words.

102
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:31,200
你知道这儿的口号
You know the motto.

103
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,670
是啊  "辛勤的蜜蜂别在这儿干活"
Yes, "Buzzing bees, sting not here."

104
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:34,900
想看不见都难
It's hard to miss.

105
00:08:34,910 --> 00:08:36,610
泰德  这几位你都认识吧
Ted, I think you know everybody.

106
00:08:36,730 --> 00:08:39,890
俗世烦恼毫无胜算  总统先生
Common woe never stood a chance. Mr. President.

107
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,490
据我所知  这是你第一次受邀
First time you've been invited, I understand.

108
00:08:42,660 --> 00:08:45,880
这句话里肯定有侮辱的意味  将军
I'm almost sure there's an insult in there somewhere, General.

109
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:46,950
泰德和我
You know, Ted and I

110
00:08:46,950 --> 00:08:49,790
刚刚在坎顿一家牛排店
just had the most remarkable piece of red meat

111
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:51,740
吃到了最好吃的红肉
at a steak house out in Canton.

112
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:54,430
我记不清了  你喜不喜欢上等肋条
I can't remember, do you like prime rib?

113
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,590
要是有合适的人陪的话
In the right company.

114
00:08:58,380 --> 00:08:59,420
先失陪了
If you'll excuse us,

115
00:08:59,420 --> 00:09:01,320
泰德和我答应本杰明
Ted and I promised young Benjamin here

116
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,550
给他点一杯成人饮料
we'd find him an adult beverage.

117
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:06,460
-喝酒吗  -还是不了
- Drink? - I'd rather not.

118
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,660
所有人都想跟将军
You know, everybody was looking forward to

119
00:09:11,660 --> 00:09:13,360
谈几句
spending some time with the general.

120
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,350
现在你也来了
And now you're here as well.

121
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:17,830
这个周末之后  谁知道呢
After this weekend, who knows?

122
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:20,200
也许这混蛋大选
Maybe this goddamn bastard of an election

123
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,980
能自行解决
will get itself resolved.

124
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,770
既然你来了
Oh, one little piece of advice

125
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:27,140
我还想给你一条小小的建议
that I could give you as long as you're out here.

126
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:31,540
要是你不招惹胡蜂  他们也不会惹你
If you don't bother the yellow jackets, they won't bother you.

127
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:40,760
你为什么不邀请康威
So why didn't you invite Conway?

128
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:43,290
被邀请的是布洛哈特
Brockhart was invited instead.

129
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:46,480
下周不会有辩论了  对吧
So there's not going to be a debate next week, is there?

130
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,180
不会有总统辩论
Not a presidential one, no.

131
00:09:50,130 --> 00:09:52,200
我真应该在俄亥俄  跟人握手
I should really be in Ohio, shaking hands.

132
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,040
你可是费了好大劲进来的  弗兰西斯
Yeah, you bargained to get in here, Francis,

133
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,820
既然你都来了  那我给你点建议
and now you're here. So let me suggest something.

134
00:09:55,820 --> 00:09:57,010
去他的俄亥俄
Fuck Ohio.

135
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,710
这就是竞选
This is the campaign.

136
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:03,960
将军是个叛徒  这你清楚
The general is a traitor, you know that.

137
00:10:04,430 --> 00:10:06,390
将军想当个政客
The general is trying to be a politician.

138
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,000
换成你也会这么做
You would have done the same.

139
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,280
对  但做得更高明
Yeah, but better.

140
00:10:17,970 --> 00:10:19,100
安德伍德总统
President Underwood?

141
00:10:20,210 --> 00:10:21,870
安德伍德总统  抱歉  女士
President Underwood? I'm sorry, ma'am,

142
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:23,850
但战况室急需你过去
but you're needed in the Situation Room.

143
00:10:33,290 --> 00:10:34,160
凯茜
Cathy.

144
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:38,000
进屋之前  我想先跟你说句话
I wanted a moment with you before we join the rest of the team.

145
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,490
-来的路上他们已经跟我说明了  -说得不全
- Oh, I was briefed on the way over. - Not fully.

146
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:42,900
一艘俄罗斯考察船受困  在下沉
A Russian research vessel is stuck and sinking--

147
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,710
对  他们声称是在采集冰芯样本
Yes, they claim they were taking core samples,

148
00:10:45,710 --> 00:10:47,520
全球变暖那套屁话
some global warming nonsense.

149
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,450
但他们其实是在勘探石油
But they were looking for oil.

150
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:51,040
他们发出了求救信号
There was a distress signal

151
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,210
然后通讯就完全中断了
and then all communication just shut down.

152
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:55,400
我们是附近唯一能发起救援的国家
We're the only country in position to rescue.

153
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,780
所以20分钟前  我们向他们提出援救
So, 20 minutes ago, we offered.

154
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:00,370
-他们不接受  -而且拒不承认
- They declined? - And denied.

155
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:03,280
佩特罗夫不希望我们知道船上有什么
Petrov does not want us to see what's on board.

156
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:07,630
我明白这决定很难做
I understand this is a difficult decision,

157
00:11:07,630 --> 00:11:09,370
但人命关天
but there are human lives at stake,

158
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:10,740
如果救援队抵达
and if help arrives,

159
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:13,400
-佩特罗夫只能被迫接受  -好吧
- Petrov will be forced to take it. - Okay.

160
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,820
谢谢  我得直接和佩特罗夫总统通话
Well, thank you. I need to speak with President Petrov directly.

161
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:22,590
海上救援  给你机会羞辱我们吗
A rescue at sea and a chance to embarrass us?

162
00:11:25,450 --> 00:11:28,250
而且就在第二次大选日前夕
Just before your second Election Day?

163
00:11:33,070 --> 00:11:35,620
感觉更像是我帮你  对吗
Sounds like I would be helping you, hmm?

164
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:38,390
船一沉  你的船员就会死
The boat sinks, your crew dies.

165
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,410
俄罗斯国内舆论会怎么样
How is that going to look at home?

166
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:44,070
我让我的人民怎么想  他们就会怎么想
I tell my people how things look, and that's how they look.

167
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:46,880
我想给你看个东西
I want to show you something.

168
00:11:47,420 --> 00:11:48,810
稍等
Wait a minute.

169
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:52,850
这个  你喜欢我的样子吗
There. Do you like my face?

170
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,670
你不适合留胡子
A beard doesn't suit you.

171
00:11:57,340 --> 00:12:00,480
不知你的人民会对你做的事有何感想
I wonder how your citizens would feel about what you've done.

172
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:03,320
我可以把你们的船员送回俄罗斯  维克多
I could return your crew to Russia, Viktor.

173
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:05,660
你把艾丹·麦卡伦还给我们
You could return Aidan Macallan.

174
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:09,220
我不喜欢量化人的价值
I don't like to quantify human worth...

175
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,960
但麦卡伦的价值确实更高
but Macallan's is higher.

176
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:16,910
社交媒体是个强大的工具
Social media is a powerful tool.

177
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:19,610
如果美国采取任何救援措施
If there is any rescue attempt by the United States,

178
00:12:19,610 --> 00:12:23,150
我就告诉俄亥俄州的人民你的真面目
I will tell the people of Ohio exactly how you look to them.

179
00:12:23,150 --> 00:12:26,560
告诉他们你是如何破坏他们州的选举的
Exactly how you disrupted their state's vote.

180
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,510
他们会相信我的
And they will believe me.

181
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,370
奥本海默也曾是成员
Oppenheimer was a member.

182
00:12:35,370 --> 00:12:36,380
那边那棵树
That tree right over there,

183
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:39,660
曼哈顿计划就是诞生在那棵树下
right under that tree, Manhattan Project was born.

184
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:43,030
而我在这颗树下小解
And right under this one, I'm relieving myself.

185
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,150
希望你不是把我和原子弹画上等号
I hope you're not equating me to the atom bomb.

186
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:52,220
你想要什么  内阁职位
What do you want? Cabinet position?

187
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:54,590
-弗兰克·安德伍德  -司法任命
- Frank Underwood-- - Judicial appointments?

188
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,910
-支持你的法案  -勿谈公事  勿谈公事
- Legislative support? - Ah, buzzing bees, buzzing bees.

189
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,790
对哦  因为曼哈顿计划
Oh, right. Because the Manhattan Project

190
00:12:58,790 --> 00:12:59,970
和商业或政治
had absolutely nothing to do

191
00:12:59,970 --> 00:13:03,700
-毫无关系  -我希望你放松
- with business or politics. - I want you to breathe.

192
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:08,630
我希望你看看月光穿过树稍的景色
I want you to look how the moonlight cuts through the trees.

193
00:13:09,930 --> 00:13:11,440
弗兰西斯  好好利用这次机会
Take this time, Francis,

194
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:13,410
了解一下其他人
to know your other attendees.

195
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:15,820
想想你究竟想做一名什么样的总统
Think about what kind of president you really want to be.

196
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,610
这样又如何
What am I supposed to do with that?

197
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,110
就是...
Just...

198
00:13:22,980 --> 00:13:25,150
你就是这么跟将军说的吗
Oh, is that what you told the general?

199
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,890
抗命
Insubordination.

200
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,280
密谋叛变
Clandestine coup.

201
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,380
对  这才是真正的领袖
Oh, yes, that's the stuff of real leadership.

202
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:33,580
有钱人喜欢军人
People with money like uniforms.

203
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:36,160
马克  告诉我他们想要什么
Mark, just tell me what they want.

204
00:13:40,970 --> 00:13:42,050
他们在等你
They're waiting for you.

205
00:14:03,830 --> 00:14:05,910
你起得真早  总统先生
You're up early, Mr. President.

206
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:08,270
习惯了
Always.

207
00:14:08,270 --> 00:14:10,950
你饿吗  我有鸡蛋
Are you hungry? I have, uh, eggs,

208
00:14:10,950 --> 00:14:14,660
还有橙汁  山蛤蜊
and orange juice, mountain oysters.

209
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:19,080
你说的是牛睾丸  对吗
You mean bull's testicles, don't you?

210
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,430
我喜欢叫它们的本名
I prefer to call things what they are.

211
00:14:23,470 --> 00:14:26,060
出人意料啊
This is unexpected.

212
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,030
我以为你会一直忙着竞选的事
I thought you'd stay out there campaigning

213
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,730
直到最后一口气
till your dying breath.

214
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:33,280
怎么  把你们丢在这荒山野岭
What, and leave you out here all alone in the wilderness

215
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:36,050
去做那些重要的决策吗
to make all these important decisions?

216
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:40,970
我以前待你不薄  雷蒙德  我希望你支持我
You've done well by me, Raymond. I'd like your support.

217
00:14:40,970 --> 00:14:42,500
是你妻子待我不薄
I've done well by your wife.

218
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:46,920
而她现在又正好是掌管白宫的人
Who happens, at this moment, to rule the White House.

219
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:50,930
别跟我说你是想拿你妻子来贿赂我
Tell me you're not peddling influence with your wife?

220
00:14:50,930 --> 00:14:55,060
你是说现在的美国代总统吗
Who, you mean the current acting President of the United States?

221
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:56,910
也就再做两周吧
For the next two weeks.

222
00:14:57,710 --> 00:15:01,730
稍有收敛  那才让人出乎意料呢
A little restraint? Now, that... that would be unexpected.

223
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,850
你的鸡蛋想怎么吃
How do you like your eggs?

224
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:05,660
下午再吃
In the afternoon.

225
00:15:05,730 --> 00:15:07,260
早上好  总统先生
Good morning, Mr. President.

226
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:10,730
在极乐之地可没有总统  不是吗
Oh, no presidents here at Elysian Fields, isn't that right?

227
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:15,150
只有前任的  或者将来的
Only former ones... or future.

228
00:15:16,430 --> 00:15:21,040
我不会把这称为政治  这只是时事
Well, I won't call this politics, then. Just current affairs.

229
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:23,910
我们有过很好的机会拿下艾哈迈迪
We had a real chance to get Ahmadi.

230
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,940
我们的团队收到简报了
Our campaign was briefed.

231
00:15:26,290 --> 00:15:28,730
你们知道得要更详细些吧
I think a little more than just briefed.

232
00:15:29,630 --> 00:15:31,520
你有多的袜子吗  雷蒙德
Do you have an extra pair of socks, Raymond?

233
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:33,460
服了30年的兵役
After 30 years of military service,

234
00:15:33,460 --> 00:15:35,160
按说我该自己备好呢
you'd think I'd arrive prepared.

235
00:15:35,380 --> 00:15:38,710
这里肯定有人能帮你找一双[胆子]
Oh, I'm sure someone around here could find you a pair.

236
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:42,220
-我的铺位下面有  -谢谢
- Under my bunk. - Thank you.

237
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,870
他是个好人
He's a good man.

238
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:55,190
很难找到不信任或不喜欢他的人
Hard to find anybody who distrusts or dislikes him.

239
00:15:59,530 --> 00:16:01,240
你到底要不要鸡蛋
So do you want eggs or not?

240
00:16:12,650 --> 00:16:13,830
以这个关税率
With this rate of tariff,

241
00:16:13,830 --> 00:16:16,280
我有信心会对反倾销案例
I'm confident it'll have a mitigating effect

242
00:16:16,290 --> 00:16:18,280
起到减震作用
on the anti-dumping cases.

243
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:20,650
我觉得这能行
I think this is going to work.

244
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:23,440
我得向我国外交部国务委员请示
I'll need to run this by my State Councilor for Foreign Affairs.

245
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,380
我认为今天对我们两国都是个好日子
I think this is a very good day for both of our countries.

246
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:27,680
是的
Yes, it is.

247
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,710
船上有个美国人
There's an American on the boat.

248
00:16:31,990 --> 00:16:33,940
那艘俄罗斯的考察船上
The Russian research vessel.

249
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:37,210
-你怎么知道的  -你进来前徐先生告诉我的
- And how do you know that? - Mr. Xu told me before you came in.

250
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:41,930
我需要证据
I will need proof of that fact.

251
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:44,170
当然  但我们告诉你
Of course, but we are only telling you

252
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,860
只是因为我们知道你们会想援救他
because we know you'll want to rescue him.

253
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:50,380
中方愿在力所能及的范围内尽量帮忙
And China is willing to help in any way we can.

254
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:53,470
我很好奇  徐先生
I'm just curious, Mr. Xu,

255
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,710
你为何如此关注这一情况
why are you so focused on this situation?

256
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,370
出于人道主义原因
For humanitarian reasons.

257
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:08,880
谢谢您的时间和合作  代总统女士
Thank you for your time and cooperation, Madam Acting President.

258
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,370
这是必要条件
It's contingent.

259
00:17:27,210 --> 00:17:29,930
如果希望部长继续关税交易
The minister won't proceed with our tariff deal

260
00:17:29,930 --> 00:17:32,800
我们必须向他保证  救援已经开展
if we don't give him assurances that the rescue is underway.

261
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,400
中方为何如此关心
Why do the Chinese care so much

262
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,480
这艘俄罗斯船上有什么
about what's on this Russian boat?

263
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:39,950
不知道  我自己也是刚知道
I don't know. I was just informed myself.

264
00:17:39,950 --> 00:17:41,390
他们在合作吗
Are they working together?

265
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:43,150
再说一次  我不知道
Again, I don't know.

266
00:17:45,090 --> 00:17:46,650
你在跟他们合作吗
Are you working with them?

267
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,540
我跟谁都合作
I work with everybody.

268
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:53,230
但这不是重点  关键是船上有个美国人
But that's beside the point. There is an American on board.

269
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:54,850
你相信吗
And you believe that?

270
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:58,410
你可不想做出错误的决定
Well, you wouldn't want to make the wrong call.

271
00:18:02,550 --> 00:18:04,500
公牛的睾丸
Bull's balls.

272
00:18:04,890 --> 00:18:06,670
一只大乌鸦
A giant crow.

273
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:10,580
还有百万富翁们呼喊着  "释我自由"
And billionaires chanting, "Set me free."

274
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:14,540
这地方真是把我无法言表的感觉都呈现出来了
Well, this place says everything I feel, but can't express.

275
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:20,100
他不可能是你的朋友
He can't be your friend.

276
00:18:20,570 --> 00:18:22,680
塔斯克没有朋友
Tusk doesn't have any friends.

277
00:18:24,450 --> 00:18:26,740
他是个...伙伴
He's, uh, an associate.

278
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:28,340
是吗
Really?

279
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:31,730
他跟你有什么伙伴关系
And how does he associate with you?

280
00:18:35,530 --> 00:18:38,300
别管那该死的蜜蜂了  没人在意它
Oh, to hell with the buzzing bees. No one else is heeding it.

281
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:40,410
一个电视台总裁  一个电信首席执行官
A network president, a telecom CEO,

282
00:18:40,410 --> 00:18:42,170
还有一个副总统候选人
the vice presidential candidate.

283
00:18:42,170 --> 00:18:43,710
你觉得他们都在聊什么
What do you think they're all talking about,

284
00:18:43,710 --> 00:18:46,640
-他们最近看的书吗  -你又在看什么
- the last book they read? - What are you reading?

285
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:50,280
你的脸
Your face...

286
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:54,100
它让我知道了你有多不想待在这里
which tells me how much you don't want to be here.

287
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:59,650
塔斯克先生曾是威尔竞选的主要捐助者
Mr. Tusk was a major donor on Will's campaign.

288
00:18:59,660 --> 00:19:03,050
嗯  所以他没受邀  这很有趣
Yes, so it's interesting that he wasn't invited.

289
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:07,420
我们在合作一个项目
We're partnering on a project.

290
00:19:07,710 --> 00:19:11,480
沙漠里的大规模数据存储中心
Large-scale data storage centers in the desert.

291
00:19:11,870 --> 00:19:12,960
太阳能的
Solar-powered.

292
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:17,640
我得去准备我的演讲
I need to get ready for my talk.

293
00:19:17,650 --> 00:19:20,770
《来世: 我们留下的》
"The Life After: What We Leave Behind."

294
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:23,050
但愿你会出席
Hope you'll be there.

295
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:29,690
你闻闻
Smell that.

296
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:32,050
高斯巴雪茄
Cohiba.

297
00:19:33,650 --> 00:19:35,030
我知道你很喜欢
I know you're a fan.

298
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:39,260
虽然我不抽了  但不代表我不能...
Even though I don't smoke anymore, doesn't mean I can't--

299
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:41,400
谁组织的这周末的聚会  你吗
Who called this weekend's gathering? You?

300
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:44,180
不是  是塔斯克
No. Tusk did.

301
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:46,660
怎么
Why?

302
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:53,130
我们觉得中国人说得对  船上的确有一位美国人
We think the Chinese are right. There is an American on board.

303
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:54,050
{\pos(160.8,86.4)}考察船

304
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:56,430
这是撒德·彼得森  两年前退休了
This is Thad Peterson. Retired two years ago.

305
00:19:56,770 --> 00:19:58,450
地球物理研究主任
Director of geophysics research

306
00:19:58,450 --> 00:20:00,400
在美国几家顶尖石油公司供职
for some of the country's top oil companies.

307
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,340
我们强烈怀疑他在那艘船上
We strongly suspect he's on board the boat.

308
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:03,990
正在和俄罗斯人合作
Working with the Russians.

309
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,420
证据呢
Where's the proof?

310
00:20:07,930 --> 00:20:10,240
这是通讯中断前
This was sent from a Russian sailor's cell phone

311
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,250
俄罗斯船员的手机发出的
before communications were cut off.

312
00:20:15,390 --> 00:20:18,380
打开无线电求救
Get on the radio and call for help!

313
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:19,790
他的妻子确认
His wife confirmed that

314
00:20:19,790 --> 00:20:22,260
录音里就是撒德·彼得森的声音
this is Thad Peterson's voice on the recording.

315
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:27,240
24小时后  最多36小时  那艘船就会沉
In 24, 36 hours tops, that boat's gone.

316
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:31,660
对  但那不能证明撒德·彼得森在船上
Yes, but that doesn't prove that Thad Peterson was on the ship.

317
00:20:34,540 --> 00:20:37,190
但女士  他是美国人
But, ma'am... he is an American--

318
00:20:37,190 --> 00:20:40,590
不  我们不能确定  除非有乘客名单
No, we can't be sure until we have a passenger manifest.

319
00:20:41,060 --> 00:20:42,930
等有更多信息再开会
Let's reconvene when you know more.

320
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:53,570
-怎么了  凯茜  -你决定不干预
- What is it, Cathy? - Your decision not to intervene.

321
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:56,050
如果有美国人在非法工作
If an American is working illegally,

322
00:20:56,050 --> 00:20:57,860
他不会出现在名单上
he will not be on the manifest--

323
00:20:57,860 --> 00:21:01,180
我还没做决定  我在等更多信息
I haven't made a decision. I'm waiting for more information.

324
00:21:02,030 --> 00:21:04,210
这关系到了艾丹·麦卡伦
This is about Aidan Macallan.

325
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:07,440
我非常确信
I am very confident

326
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:10,210
中国谎称有美国人在船上
China is lying about an American being on board.

327
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:12,210
船上有他们想要的东西
There is something on that boat they want

328
00:21:12,210 --> 00:21:14,580
得等我知道是什么再说
and I can't proceed until I know what it is.

329
00:21:14,830 --> 00:21:18,150
他们说自己的动机是救人
They say they're motivated by saving human lives.

330
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:19,810
但那不是他们的真实动机
But that's not what's driving them.

331
00:21:20,670 --> 00:21:22,250
我只是觉得难以接受
And I just find it so frustrating

332
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:25,650
人命受到如此漠视
when human life is treated with such disregard.

333
00:21:27,330 --> 00:21:28,560
抱歉  但...
We're sorry. But...

334
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:32,650
俗话说的"林间漫步"不适合我
The proverbial walk in the woods is not for me.

335
00:21:32,870 --> 00:21:35,740
在林荫小径寻寻觅觅
Navel-gazing on some forest path.

336
00:21:35,740 --> 00:21:39,540
思考死亡与永生
Contemplating mortality. Immortality.

337
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:42,950
才不  历史要去争取
No. History is earned.

338
00:21:42,950 --> 00:21:45,400
赢了今天  然后再去赢明天
You win the day, and then you win the day after,

339
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,940
日复一日  至死方休
and you do the same thing every day until you're dead.

340
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:49,820
你被载入史册  不是因为你总赢
And you're remembered not for the winning,

341
00:21:49,820 --> 00:21:51,580
而是因为你从不输
but because you never lost.

342
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:53,760
好了
Now...

343
00:21:58,940 --> 00:21:59,900
道格
Doug?

344
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,460
道格  能听到吗
Doug, can you hear me?

345
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:05,490
我现在需要些筹码
I need some leverage out here right now.

346
00:22:05,710 --> 00:22:08,560
-怎么了  -康威完了
- What's going on? - Conway is finished.

347
00:22:08,830 --> 00:22:09,620
如果他们胜选
If they win,

348
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:11,110
布洛哈特会操控大局
Brockhart will do all the heavy lifting.

349
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:12,650
他会成为真正的总统
He'll essentially be the president.

350
00:22:12,650 --> 00:22:14,110
我们该利用对手研究信息
We should have used the oppo.

351
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:17,280
听着  布洛哈特是塔斯克挑的人
Listen, Brockhart is Tusk's pick.

352
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:20,280
我得找办法逼那老头支持我
I need to find a way to force that old man to support me.

353
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:23,480
-先生  总统先生  -听得到吗
- Sir? Mr. President? - Do you hear me?

354
00:22:30,740 --> 00:22:31,390
我在听
I'm here.

355
00:22:31,390 --> 00:22:33,420
塔斯克和波利跳达成了交易
Tusk has some deal with Pollyhop.

356
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:35,550
我需要想办法阻止他们
I need to find a way to stop that.

357
00:22:35,550 --> 00:22:37,200
发个行政命令
An executive order...

358
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:43,340
先生
Sir?

359
00:22:46,730 --> 00:22:48,070
稍有收敛
A little restraint...

360
00:22:49,770 --> 00:22:51,460
那才让人出乎意料
would be unexpected.

361
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:55,510
总统先生
Mr. President?

362
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:57,510
-道格  -先生
- Doug. - Sir?

363
00:22:57,860 --> 00:22:59,190
什么都别做
Don't do anything.

364
00:23:00,020 --> 00:23:01,180
我不明白
I don't understand.

365
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,480
什么都别做  等我的指令
Don't do anything until you hear from me.

366
00:23:03,720 --> 00:23:07,120
-先生  波利跳交易怎么办  -听见了吗
- Sir, what about the Pollyhop deal? - Do you hear me?

367
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:09,500
-什么都别...  -总统先生  我
- Don't do anything... - Mr. President, I...

368
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:22,290
你打回去了吗
Have you tried calling him back?

369
00:23:22,290 --> 00:23:24,660
没人接  我们该做什么
There's no answer. What should we do?

370
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:27,300
什么都不做  总统既然说了  那就听他的
Nothing. That's what the president said, so that's what we'll do.

371
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:29,800
-让护卫把他撤出来吗  -不  我们等着
- Should we have his team pull him out? - No. We wait.

372
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:31,580
夫人
Ma'am...

373
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:34,490
-如果我们没能妥当处置营救的事  -道格
- if we don't handle this rescue correctly... - Doug.

374
00:23:34,490 --> 00:23:37,200
让我想办法让总统和佩特罗夫通上电话
Let me find a way to get the president on the phone with Petrov.

375
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,330
不  弗兰西斯不需要分心
No. Francis doesn't need this distraction.

376
00:23:39,330 --> 00:23:40,480
我不同意
I disagree.

377
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:42,270
我知道你不同意
I know you do.

378
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:46,300
人说三代之后就没人会记得我们了
They say we're only remembered for three generations.

379
00:23:46,390 --> 00:23:50,140
那一个人该做些什么才能不被忘却呢
What would one have to do not to be forgotten?

380
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:52,900
小本杰明知道未来是啥样
Young Benjamin here knows what's coming.

381
00:23:54,090 --> 00:23:56,360
谁在乎他没听说过约翰尼·卡森[主持人]
Who cares if he's never heard of Johnny Carson?

382
00:23:58,490 --> 00:23:59,690
可怜的老塔斯克
Poor old Tusk.

383
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:02,960
别看他嬉皮笑脸的  但他可骗不了我
He wears that game face, but he doesn't fool me.

384
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:06,480
未来让他恐惧  因为他知道自己时日无多
The future terrifies him because he knows it's short.

385
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:09,970
声明一下  我知道约翰尼·卡森是谁
For the record, I have heard of Johnny Carson.

386
00:24:09,970 --> 00:24:12,500
他每天晚上哄我爸妈上床
He tucked my parents into bed every night.

387
00:24:17,390 --> 00:24:19,840
我今天得到了特别的许可
I've been given special permission

388
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:22,290
向大家展示我们的成果
to show you what we've been working on.

389
00:24:22,290 --> 00:24:27,100
想象这样一种可能  你的大脑  你的意识
Imagine the possibility of your brain, your consciousness,

390
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:29,300
都实时进行数字化存储
stored digitally in real time.

391
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:31,930
永生究竟是什么
I mean, what is immortality?

392
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:35,130
终有一日  格兰特的设想也会过时
In time, even Grant's vision will get old.

393
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:39,090
早晚的事  谁都免不了
It will happen, as it does for all of us.

394
00:24:39,090 --> 00:24:40,830
这还只是早期版本
Now this is still in the early stages,

395
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:43,480
但我们一直在收集储存
but we've been collecting and storing

396
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:47,830
雷蒙德的记忆  想法  怪癖和爱好
Raymond's memories, thoughts, quirks and tics.

397
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:51,460
这还只是实验版本  但最终
This is a mock-up. But eventually...

398
00:24:55,250 --> 00:24:56,700
这个雷蒙德
this Raymond...

399
00:24:57,030 --> 00:25:00,400
会像各位眼前这位一样活生生
will feel as real as the one standing before you.

400
00:25:01,010 --> 00:25:04,470
我更喜欢脚踏实地
I like dirt and rocks...

401
00:25:06,340 --> 00:25:07,810
货真价实
and facts.

402
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,900
这我也同意
No argument here.

403
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:14,780
我只相信能抓在手里的  或者能亲眼看到的
I trust only what I can hold in my hand or see on my horizon.

404
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:18,180
但你不能光干坐着看风景啊
Well, but you can't just sit back and admire the view.

405
00:25:18,470 --> 00:25:22,260
我就发现一定要紧抓当下
I've learned you've got to grab the present by the balls.

406
00:25:22,260 --> 00:25:24,280
那才是美国人民在乎的
That's where the American people live.

407
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:27,410
你更像个推销员而不是总统  总统先生
You sound more like a salesman than a president, Mr. President.

408
00:25:27,410 --> 00:25:29,940
我们是美国人  我们就是推销员
Well, if we're Americans, then we are salesmen, right?

409
00:25:29,940 --> 00:25:31,350
这是我们天生的权利
That's our birthright.

410
00:25:31,350 --> 00:25:34,560
卖车  卖手机  卖汽油
Cars and phones and a gallon of gas.

411
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:36,570
我眼里的美国可不是这样
That's not how I see America.

412
00:25:37,090 --> 00:25:38,600
我是爱国者  我为国效力
I'm a patriot. I serve.

413
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:40,090
那我们向你致敬  将军
Well, then, we salute you, General.

414
00:25:40,090 --> 00:25:42,780
但你为国效力的意义是什么
But you serve to what purpose?

415
00:25:42,780 --> 00:25:45,400
不还是为了其他美国人能去推销
So the rest of America can sell.

416
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,790
你看  这个周末  你和我
I mean, you and I, right now, this weekend,

417
00:25:47,790 --> 00:25:50,840
不就在这个营地推销自己吗
we're here at this camp selling ourselves.

418
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:54,110
人的品质不言自明
Character speaks for itself.

419
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,150
人民需要一个他们能信赖的总统
People want a president they can trust.

420
00:25:56,150 --> 00:25:59,080
错  不对  他们需要一个他们了解的总统
No, they don't. They want a president they know.

421
00:25:59,830 --> 00:26:01,460
而我也了解他们
And I know them.

422
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:05,120
我唯一感兴趣的未来就是接下来的四年
The only future I'm interested in is the next four years.

423
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:08,520
所以没错  我明天要推销  后天接着推销
So, yes, I'm selling tomorrow and the day after that

424
00:26:08,530 --> 00:26:10,230
大后天还要推销
and the day after that.

425
00:26:10,230 --> 00:26:13,190
我是在推销一个曾经住在桃子农场的男孩
I'm selling a boy who used to live on a peach farm

426
00:26:13,190 --> 00:26:15,290
而他现在住在白宫
who now lives in the White House.

427
00:26:15,290 --> 00:26:17,180
我要推销一个
I'm selling a tomorrow

428
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:21,290
可触可感的明天
that you can see and touch and feel.

429
00:26:21,670 --> 00:26:22,570
要是你把这个夺走
Now, you take that away,

430
00:26:22,570 --> 00:26:25,260
我不知道这国家还剩下什么
and I don't know what this country has left.

431
00:26:25,890 --> 00:26:28,010
只剩下一群成年男人
Except a group of grown men

432
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:32,500
围成一圈  盯着一小块屏幕
standing around in a circle, all staring at a small screen.

433
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,860
只向内看  而不往外面看
Looking in instead of looking out.

434
00:26:34,860 --> 00:26:38,740
那随时给我盖一把黄土吧
Heck, give me a peck of dirt any day of the week.

435
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:42,840
说得好  敬黄土
Hear, hear. To a peck of dirt.

436
00:26:42,850 --> 00:26:44,890
-说得好  -我要敬这一杯
- Hear, hear. - I will drink to that,

437
00:26:44,890 --> 00:26:49,780
也要敬将军一杯  他是位优秀的公仆
but I will also drink to the general, a good servant.

438
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:51,140
敬将军
To the general.

439
00:26:53,550 --> 00:26:56,730
我敢肯定  这一交易随时可能落空
I promise you, this deal is on the verge of falling apart.

440
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,070
就在重新投票之前
Right before your revote.

441
00:26:59,410 --> 00:27:01,840
我只是个传话的
I... I'm only the messenger, by the way.

442
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:04,980
我们不能让这笔交易落空
We can't let this deal fall apart.

443
00:27:04,980 --> 00:27:09,180
没错  但我们必须马上救援
Agreed. But the rescue has to happen immediately.

444
00:27:09,180 --> 00:27:11,480
你好像跟这事有利益关系
You seem personally invested in this.

445
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:15,050
不不  我只是在寻找解决方案
Oh, no, no. I'm just looking for a solution.

446
00:27:18,260 --> 00:27:19,520
我有个想法
I had a thought.

447
00:27:20,850 --> 00:27:23,610
我愿意让驻扎在乔治王岛的
I would be willing to allow the Chinese sailors

448
00:27:23,610 --> 00:27:27,380
中国船员登上我们的破冰船
that are stationed on King George Island to board our icebreaker.

449
00:27:27,820 --> 00:27:30,290
然后  在内部摄像机前
Then, purely for the in-house cameras,

450
00:27:30,290 --> 00:27:33,270
摆出是中国领导了此次救援的样子
we let it appear as though the Chinese led the rescue.

451
00:27:33,270 --> 00:27:34,230
当然  自始至终
Now, of course, the whole time,

452
00:27:34,230 --> 00:27:37,210
都会是美国控制船
the Americans would remain in charge of the boat,

453
00:27:37,210 --> 00:27:40,030
但不必让俄罗斯人知道我们参与了
but the Russians don't need to know our involvement.

454
00:27:40,030 --> 00:27:42,680
我觉得这是可以接受的
I imagine that would be acceptable.

455
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:46,920
我马上就向徐先生转达
I'll relay this scenario to Mr. Xu immediately.

456
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:50,480
我还想把关税凑整成20%
But I'd also like to round up the tariff to 20%.

457
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:53,920
我们已经商定19%了
We have a firm deal at 19.

458
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:57,980
我知道  但突然间  这似乎不够高
I know. But suddenly, it just doesn't seem high enough.

459
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:01,140
我觉得他们会答应的
I think they'll be okay with it.

460
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:05,620
祈祷如此吧  我尽力
Fingers crossed. I'll do my best.

461
00:28:06,260 --> 00:28:09,450
-还挺顺利的  -是啊  非常顺利
- That went rather well, I think. - It did. It went very well.

462
00:28:09,890 --> 00:28:11,820
你超出了所有人的预料
You've exceeded everyone's expectations,

463
00:28:11,830 --> 00:28:14,400
整个周末你的表现很出色  但是
the way you handled yourself all weekend, but...

464
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,490
他们能预料布洛哈特的一举一动
Brockhart's someone they can predict.

465
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:25,560
话先别说太早  这事还没完
Don't get ahead of yourself. This is not over.

466
00:28:25,790 --> 00:28:28,380
你要干什么  弗兰西斯  你要利用对手研究吗
What are you gonna do, Francis? Are you gonna use the oppo?

467
00:28:28,380 --> 00:28:31,070
你似乎很着急嘛
Well, it seems to have worried you enough.

468
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:33,430
他还只是副总统候选人
He's still only the vice presidential candidate.

469
00:28:35,010 --> 00:28:36,270
我要走了
I'm leaving.

470
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:39,410
-你不用走的  -我知道  什么都不是必须的
- You don't have to go. - No, I know. I don't have to do anything.

471
00:28:41,150 --> 00:28:43,060
你记得我们第一次见面的情景吧
Do you remember when we first met?

472
00:28:43,060 --> 00:28:45,520
你差一点就加入我第二次竞选了
You almost joined my second campaign.

473
00:28:45,520 --> 00:28:47,910
我们坐在加夫尼的便宜馆子里
We sat down at that little greasy spoon in Gaffney.

474
00:28:47,910 --> 00:28:50,730
记得  要是你招了我  肯定就大获全胜了
Yeah, if you'd signed me on, you would have won by a landslide.

475
00:28:50,730 --> 00:28:54,580
我还是赢了  因为我从不输
I won anyway, because I never lose.

476
00:28:54,810 --> 00:28:56,990
你知道当时我为什么没雇你吗
You know why I didn't hire you back then?

477
00:28:57,270 --> 00:28:59,400
因为你去结账的时候
Because when you went to pick up the check,

478
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:01,660
你告诉我不用给你钱
you told me I didn't have to pay you.

479
00:29:01,660 --> 00:29:05,340
你愿意不要报酬为我工作  我不信
That you would work for free. I don't trust that.

480
00:29:05,850 --> 00:29:07,980
因为谁也不会不要报酬
Because no one works for free.

481
00:29:10,150 --> 00:29:13,910
总统女士  恐怕我不能同意20%
Madam President, I'm afraid I can't agree to 20%.

482
00:29:13,910 --> 00:29:17,070
-对经济的影响  -我们陷入僵局了
- The economic implications-- - We're at an impasse.

483
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:21,230
我很希望能继续对话  但与此同时
I'm willing to keep the conversation going, but in the meantime--

484
00:29:21,230 --> 00:29:23,700
你们不同意  我们就不行动
We'll do nothing until you agree.

485
00:29:24,610 --> 00:29:26,740
总统女士  会有人丧命的
Madam President, people will die.

486
00:29:26,740 --> 00:29:29,690
所以我才惊讶你居然不同意我的条件
Which is why I'm surprised you won't agree to my terms.

487
00:29:29,690 --> 00:29:31,760
除非外交部国务委员同意
I can't agree to the terms without the approval

488
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:34,450
否则我不能同意你的条件
of my State Councillor for Foreign Affairs.

489
00:29:36,850 --> 00:29:40,580
船上有112人
There are 112 people aboard the vessel.

490
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:43,180
要是算上彼得森先生就是113人
113 if you count Mr. Peterson.

491
00:29:44,190 --> 00:29:48,010
20至32小时后  船就会完全沉没
Now, it will go under in 20 to 32 hours.

492
00:29:48,010 --> 00:29:50,770
现在南冰洋的水温
The temperature of the Southern Ocean right now

493
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:52,360
是零下2摄氏度
is 28 degrees Fahrenheit.

494
00:29:52,370 --> 00:29:56,490
在这么冷的水里  人不到45分钟
A body will freeze to death within 45 minutes

495
00:29:56,490 --> 00:29:58,010
就会冻死
in water that cold.

496
00:29:58,010 --> 00:30:01,370
更不要说在冻死之前早就失去游泳能力了
And, of course, one loses the ability to swim long before that.

497
00:30:05,320 --> 00:30:07,250
徐部长  你还在吗
Minister Xu, are you still there?

498
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:13,630
和佩特罗夫总统合谋永远是个错误
Collaborating with President Petrov is always a mistake.

499
00:30:13,630 --> 00:30:16,740
20%的关税会帮你们长长记性
The 20% tariff will help you keep that in mind.

500
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,980
我等你回复
I'm waiting.

501
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:22,220
这些人的死活取决于你了
It's up to you if they live or die.

502
00:30:30,470 --> 00:30:33,020
-船员呢  -全部获救
- The crew? - All rescued.

503
00:30:34,730 --> 00:30:35,850
撒德·彼得森呢
And Thad Peterson?

504
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:38,060
你猜的没错  中国人在撒谎
You were right. The Chinese were lying.

505
00:30:38,060 --> 00:30:40,700
只有他仍然下落不明
He's the only one still unaccounted for.

506
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,970
上将说还有机会拯救那艘船
The admiral says there's still a chance to save the boat.

507
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:51,110
让它沉吧
Let it go down.

508
00:30:52,410 --> 00:30:54,430
那佩特罗夫放在船上的东西呢
And whatever Petrov has on it?

509
00:30:54,430 --> 00:30:56,320
我们这么做是对的  凯茜
We're doing the right thing, Cathy.

510
00:30:57,760 --> 00:30:59,680
你已经达到目的了  维克多
You got what you wanted, Viktor.

511
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:03,420
船已经沉了  让我们接着往下谈吧
The boat is gone. Now let's get back to where we left off.

512
00:31:03,630 --> 00:31:07,840
你想要什么  才能换艾丹·麦卡伦回国
What will it take to get Aidan Macallan back on American soil?

513
00:31:10,940 --> 00:31:12,300
他挺喜欢这里的
He likes it here.

514
00:31:26,620 --> 00:31:28,280
要走了吗  总统先生
Leaving, Mr. President?

515
00:31:31,790 --> 00:31:33,740
先放车上吧  谢谢
You can put that in the car, thank you.

516
00:31:36,030 --> 00:31:39,180
-你没事吧  -好多了
